Commit Message: Extract hyde markdown extensions from markdown fork.

Use `hydedown` as the top level package.

Namespace packages seem to bring about a lot of hurt and there isn't
any good reason not to use a different but simple top level
package name.

Remove recursion for pypy compatibility.

The `assemble` function in `sections` module recurses to modify the
element tree to include sections and hgroups. Given `pypy`'s low
recursion depth support, its better to use a non recursive depth
first traversal of the element tree.

- Make `assemble` non recursive
- Ensure all element checks are against `None` to remove
  `FutureWarnings`
- Add a simple test for `sections`
- Ensure tests run on pypy

Ensure `makeExtension` takes kwargs.

- Change `makeExtension` function to take kwargs for markdown 2.6.x
  compatibility.
- Fix PEP8 issues
- Add setup.cfg to ignore line length warnings
